    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 1.3L 13B-REW rotary engine with its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger setup. This example retains its factory-spec vacuum routing and shows exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The chassis remains telepathic, utilizing its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential. Finished in its period-correct original paint with no signs of oxidation or structural fatigue, this FD delivers the pure, high-revving engagement of a 90s JDM legend. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history ensuring the integrity of the apex seals and cooling system.",
